<TITLE> 'Dacoit boss' killed in shootout with Ctg police </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Jan 11 (bdnews24.com)  A suspected leader of a robber gang was killed in a gunfight with police at Hathajari in Chittagong early on Monday. The deceased has been identified only as 'Khalil' alias 'Sohel', 37. Another suspect Abul Hossain was also injured during the gun battle and admitted to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. Babul Akhter, Hathajari circle assistant superintendent of police, told bdnews24.com that police launched a raid at Bahbanipur village in the upazila at around 1:30am, acting on a tip-off that Khalil and his associates were planning a robbery. Akhter said the suspects shot at the law enforcers, who returned fire. Khalil and Abul Hossain were both taken to CMCH, where the duty doctor declared him dead, said the police officer. Police recovered two foreign and four locally made handguns and 33 rounds of ammunition from the scene, the police official sai
